===========================================================

 1). Minimum requirements
 
  o Java 1.5 or later 
  		-- Any operating system on which Java runs is supported.  	
  o lib/xbird-db-xx.jar and lib/commons-logging-xx.jar

  For details, visit the following page:

	http://code.google.com/p/xbird/wiki/LibraryDependencyListing

 2). Getting started

  A QuickStart can be found on the following page:
	
	http://code.google.com/p/xbird/wiki/QuickStart
	
 3). Building XBird 
 
  XBird is being developed with the Eclipse environment. 
  
  You can configure the environment by just importing this package 
  as a Java project. Then, project -> Build Project compiles XBird
  classes.

 3). Credits

  See http://code.google.com/p/xbird/ for the list of XBird contributors.

  If you want to be a developer of XBird, contact me <yuin405@gmail.com> 
  freely with your patches.
